Pudo - I'm not sure what's meant here. Are you talking about moderation for new users? Or some other sort of enforcement? Is it spam you want to target?
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The links you're concerned about - are they the spam ones in the User's 'about' field? If so, I think we *should* allow users to have links, although continue with applying them with 'nofollow' and attack spammers back in a concerted strategy across all editable fields - see ticket &lt;a class="new ticket" href="http://localhost/ticket/1257" title="enhancement: Anti-Spam tools (new)"&gt;#1257&lt;/a&gt;.
